OVERVIEW
------------------------------------------------------------
Elden Ring is a dark fantasy action role-playing game set in
the Lands Between, a vast open world crafted through a
collaboration between legendary game director Hidetaka Miyazaki
(known for the Dark Souls series and Bloodborne) and acclaimed
fantasy novelist George R.R. Martin (author of A Song of Ice
and Fire). Players take on the role of a "Tarnished," an exiled
warrior summoned back to the Lands Between to seek the shards
of the shattered Elden Ring and ultimately become the Elden Lord.

The game expands on FromSoftware's signature "Soulslike" formula
by introducing a massive open world filled with dungeons, legacy
dungeons (large structured areas akin to classic FromSoftware
levels), hidden secrets, and an enormous variety of enemies and
bosses. Players can explore on horseback using their spectral
steed, Torrent, and freely shape their character build through
a deep RPG system featuring weapons, sorceries, incantations,
and Ashes of War.

